ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class HeldEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.HeldEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class HeldEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Indicates that an existing call has been put on hold.

    The only supported parameters for the HeldEvent are:

    HeldEvent Supported Parameters
    monitorCrossRefID Mandatory Associates the event to an established monitor.
    heldConnection Mandatory Specifies the connection at which the hold was activated.
    holdingDevice Mandatory Specifies the device at which the hold was activated.
    localConnectionInfo Conditional Specifies the local connection state of the device associated with the Monitor Cross Reference ID.
    cause Mandatory Specifies the reason for the event.

    EventCause values:

    • NORMAL: Indicates that the event report occurred at a bridged device or the call has not yet been transferred. Note this is added for completeness but bridging is not supported.
    • CONFERENCE: The call was held at the device with the intended purpose of establishing a conference
    • TRANSFER: The call was held at the device with the intended purpose of transferring the call

    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
